response.overview: After nearly a century in heavy industry, the Zidell family is poised for their most ambitious project yet, one where they won't be building a steel barge, but rather a community. This is the remarkable story of how commercial success and the application of environmental science to a major industrial site brought them to this moment, one that is essentially about generational values, civic stewardship, and giving back to the city they call home.
response.title: Built by Zidell
